---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy notice — TrustNotch"
  description="Privacy notice for the TrustNotch public website (trustnotch.com): what data is processed, why, and your rights under GDPR."
  canonicalPath="/privacy"
>
  <div class="page-wrapper">

    <!-- Hero -->
    <section class="section hero" aria-labelledby="privacy-hero-heading">
      <div class="section__label">Legal</div>
      <h1 id="privacy-hero-heading">Privacy notice</h1>
      <p class="hero__sub">
        This notice covers the public website <strong>trustnotch.com</strong>.
        It describes what personal data this site processes, on what basis,
        and what rights you have. It does not cover the TrustNotch product,
        API, or customer dashboard (<code>app.trustnotch.com</code>) — those
        are governed by the service agreement between TrustNotch and its
        customers.
      </p>
      <p class="updated">Last updated: <time datetime="2026-06-30">30 June 2026</time> — draft, pending legal review.</p>
    </section>

    <!-- Controller -->
    <section class="section" aria-labelledby="controller-heading">
      <div class="section__label">Controller</div>
      <h2 id="controller-heading" class="section__heading">Who is responsible for your data</h2>
      <div class="prose">
        <p>
          The data controller for this website is
          <strong>Kamala 2024 OOD</strong>,
          a company registered in Bulgaria
          (ul. Georgi Dimitrov 1, s. Eleshnitsa, obsht. Razlog, obl. Blagoevgrad, Bulgaria).
        </p>
        <p>
          For privacy-related questions or to exercise your rights, contact us at
          <strong><a href="mailto:privacy@trustnotch.com">privacy@trustnotch.com</a></strong>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Cookies & tracking -->
    <section class="section" aria-labelledby="cookies-heading">
      <div class="section__label">Cookies &amp; tracking</div>
      <h2 id="cookies-heading" class="section__heading">No cookies, no analytics, no trackers</h2>
      <div class="prose">
        <p>
          This site uses <strong>no cookies</strong>, no analytics tools, and no
          third-party trackers or embeds of any kind. All assets — fonts, styles,
          scripts — are self-hosted; loading a page on trustnotch.com makes no
          requests to any third-party server.
        </p>
        <p>
          Because nothing on this site requires your consent under ePrivacy or
          GDPR, there is no cookie banner or consent pop-up — that is by design,
          not an oversight.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- What we process -->
    <section class="section" aria-labelledby="processing-heading">
      <div class="section__label">Data processing</div>
      <h2 id="processing-heading" class="section__heading">What we do process</h2>

      <h3 class="subsection-title">Web server access logs</h3>
      <div class="prose">
        <p>
          This website (<strong>trustnotch.com</strong>) is served as static files
          and <strong>does not keep access logs</strong>. The web server is not
          configured to record visits to the site, so no IP addresses or request
          metadata from browsing these pages are stored.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Hosting:</strong> the site is hosted in the EU
          (Hetzner, Helsinki, Finland). No data is transferred outside the
          European Economic Area. TrustNotch's separate API and dashboard
          services (<code>api.trustnotch.com</code>, <code>app.trustnotch.com</code>)
          do keep short-lived request logs for security and operation; those are
          covered by the customer service agreement, not this website notice.
        </p>
      </div>

      <h3 class="subsection-title mt-section">Email contact</h3>
      <div class="prose">
        <p>
          If you contact us via the email link on this site, we receive and process
          whatever you include in that message — typically your email address and
          the content you write — in order to respond to you.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Legal basis:</strong> legitimate interest (Article 6(1)(f) GDPR) —
          responding to an inbound enquiry you initiated.
        </p>
        <p>
          We do not add you to any mailing list from a contact email. We retain
          correspondence for as long as it is reasonably needed for the purpose you
          contacted us about, then delete it.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Rights -->
    <section class="section" aria-labelledby="rights-heading">
      <div class="section__label">Your rights</div>
      <h2 id="rights-heading" class="section__heading">Rights under GDPR</h2>
      <div class="prose">
        <p>
          Under GDPR you have the right to: access the personal data we hold about
          you; have inaccurate data corrected; request erasure where there is no
          overriding legitimate ground to retain it; restrict processing in certain
          circumstances; object to processing based on legitimate interest; and, where
          processing is based on consent, to withdraw that consent without affecting
          the lawfulness of prior processing.
        </p>
        <p>
          To exercise any of these rights, contact us at
          <strong><a href="mailto:privacy@trustnotch.com">privacy@trustnotch.com</a></strong>.
          We will respond within the timeframe required by GDPR (generally one month).
        </p>
        <p>
          You also have the right to lodge a complaint with your national supervisory
          authority. As TrustNotch is registered in Bulgaria, the lead supervisory
          authority is the <strong>Commission for Personal Data Protection (CPDP)</strong>
          — <a href="https://www.cpdp.bg" rel="noopener noreferrer">www.cpdp.bg</a>.
          If you are based in another EU/EEA member state, you may also contact your
          local authority.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Changes -->
    <section class="section last-section" aria-labelledby="changes-heading">
      <div class="section__label">Changes</div>
      <h2 id="changes-heading" class="section__heading">Updates to this notice</h2>
      <div class="prose">
        <p>
          If we change how we process data on this site, we will update this page
          and revise the "last updated" date at the top. Material changes will be
          flagged where we reasonably can.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .hero { padding-block-start: clamp(3rem, 8vw, 5rem); }
  .hero__sub {
    font-size: clamp(1rem, 2.5vw, 1.1875rem);
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    max-width: 58ch;
    margin-top: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .updated {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
  }

  .prose {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.875rem;
  }
  .prose p {
    color: var(--color-text-secondary);
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    max-width: 68ch;
  }

  .subsection-title {
    font-size: 1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-top: 1.75rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }
  .mt-section { margin-top: 2.25rem; }

  .last-section { border-bottom: none; }
</style>
